      },
      "text": [
        " اللَّهِ عَزَّ وَ جَلَّ وَ مَنْ يَكْتُمْها فَإِنَّهُ آثِمٌ قَلْبُهُ قَالَ بَعْدَ الشَّهَادَةِ ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Ali Bin Ibrahim, from his father, from Ibn Abu Umeyr, from Hisham Bin Salim, ",
          "(It has been narrated) from Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup> regarding the Words of Allah<sup>azwj</sup> Mighty and Majestic <span class=\"ibTxt\"><a href=\"/#/books/quran:2#h283\">[2:283]</a> and whoever conceals it, so he has a sinful heart</span>. He<sup>asws</sup> said: ‘After the witnessing’."
        ],
        "en.sarwar": [
          "2. Afi ibn Ibrahim has narrated from his father from ibn abu ‘Umayr from Hisham ibn Salim who has narrated the following: “About the meaning of the words of Allah, most Majestic, most Glorious, ‘. . . one who hides a testimony his heart is sinful,’ (2: 283) abu ‘Abd Allah, Alayhi al-Salam, has said, ‘It is after having witnessed a case.’” "
        ]
      }
